name: Encrypted DigiDoc File
summary: A CDOC file is an encrypted digital document (DigiDoc) created with qDigiDoc, an open source software used to authenticate Estonian and Finnish government issued ID cards and signed documents. It contains a data file (an .XML, .DOC, .XLS, .PDF, .RTF, etc.) encrypted with the AES-128 encryption algorithm, an encrypted key to decrypt the data file, recipient certificate, and other metadata.
